-- Azerbaijan Raises Minimum Capital Requirement for Banks Fivefold
-- B y   Z u l f u g a r   A g a y e v
-- 2012-08-03T11:52:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-03/azerbaijan-raises-minimum-capital-requirement-for-banks-fivefold.html
Azerbaijan ’s central bank raised the
minimum consolidated capital required for banks to operate in
the Caspian Sea nation fivefold to 50 million manat ($64
million).  The minimum statutory capital for opening banks was also
increased five times to the same amount, the central bank said
in an e-mailed statement today.  The decision, taken during a July 25 meeting of the central
bank’s board, takes effect Jan. 1, 2014, the bank said.  Azerbaijan is the third-largest oil producer in the former
 Soviet Union  after Russia and Kazakhstan.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zulfugar Agayev in Baku at 
